The paper deals with problems related to graph connectivity and optimization, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The use of approximation algorithms and hardness results suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.NE (Networks and Economics), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
